SIMPLE: supposititious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supposititious
<hw>Sup*pos`i*ti"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>suppositicus</ets>. See <er>Supposition</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Fraudulently substituted for something else; not being what is
purports to be; not genuine; spurious; counterfeit; <as>as, a
<ex>supposititious</ex> child; a <ex>supposititious</ex>
writing</as>.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Suppositional; hypothetical.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sup*pos`i*ti"tious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sup*pos`i*ti"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suppositive</ent>⟦br⟧
